ngine oil pressure for the cranks shaft bearing supply to the lower half of the cylinders  we replace all  parts with only two assembly csrv rotating shafts and two floating seals for each cylinder  greater volumetric efficiency up to double that of the poppet valve has been achieved  utilizing higher compression ratios of  to  and up to  to   poppet valve engines in vehicles using gasoline are approximately  to  caterpillar cummins  to  operating on natural gas and only operate as stand by emergency systems and not constant operating service  the coates csrv engines have been independently tested and have proven results with more hp higher rpms lower fuel consumption higher thermal efficiencies while producing lower harmful emissions released into our atmosphere  the coates csrv engines operate on natural gas cng lng propane hydrogen gasoline diesel and a combination of these fuels  poppet valves cannot operate higher than  to  compression ratio operating on lng cng because the poppet valves are constantly in the combustion chamber and get red hot when the constant temperature of the combustion chamber exceeds ° f when it does it manufactures no x oxides of nitrogen and co carbon monoxide and uses much more fuel the engine thermal efficiency is reduced  the governments around the world are asking the impossible of the poppet engine  the coates csrv spherical rotary valve system constantly rotates away from the combustion chamber heat using incoming air to cool the inlet and cooling the exhaust with a water cooling system through the center of the exhaust assembly shaft  gallons of water per minute  there is no servicing or adjusting or maintenance to the csrv system for the life of the engine  engine oil changes are extended to  miles or more  the reason poppet valve engines do not last operating on natural gas this fuel does not have any lubricating properties contained in it  as a result number  piston rings in poppet valve engines wear out in a very short time  