les or laws of science energy in less energy out here at coates rd plant we have come up with a new invention that weakens the quantum electromagnetic covalent bond of the atomic structure of molecules in water ho in water molecules the oxygen atom attracts the electrons in an oh covalent bond the hydrogen has no inner shell of electrons to shield the nucleus and there is an electrostatic interaction between the hydrogen proton and the single pair of electrons on the oxygen atom in the associate molecules each oxygen atom has two associates pairs of electrons and can make hydrogen bond to two different hydrogen atoms the strengths of hydrogen bonds are about one tenth of the strengths of normal covalent bonds hydrogen bonding does have significant effects on physical properties it accounts for the unusual properties of water and for the relatively high boiling point of ho hf and nh compared with hs hc and phwe have come up with a new device that weakens the covalent bond in water ho molecules making it much easier to split water into hydrogen in larger quantities in a shorter time period this new apparatus does not include more energy in to produce hydrogen it requires less energy in to split water into hydrogen  no new energy is required to weaken the covalent bong of the water molecules we expect to have the new reactor ready for testing in the next two weeks we already have csrv® engines operating on water split into hydrogen so we know it worksthe chinese new year starts today we believe it will go on for two weeks we are ready to go when they are letters of intent preliminary agreements and nondisclosure agreements have all been signed and will be posted on our edgar filingsthe company is continuing talks with financers here in the usa for funding the start up of production here in americaorders are still coming in for our natural gas industrial csrv® engine generators from the oil and gas industry we are now requesting  deposits with five months delivery timew